| Mondays and Fridays 15.30 until it stops after screening episode 215? on Monday 13 June 1988. Replaced with locally made [[Password (TV series)|Password]]. Series returns on Wednesday 03/08/88 at 15.30 and is shown on Wednesdays, Thursdays and Fridays. Then Mondays, Tuesdays and Wednesdays 12.30 from 10 October 1988 in the slot vacated by [[The Sullivans]]. After episode on Wednesday 28 December 1988 series has two episodes shown on Tuesday 3 January and Wednesday 4 January at 15.30 for only two episode. Series returns on Tuesday 14 February twice weekly at 12.30.  One a week in late 1989???, Tuesdays, Wednesdays and Thursdays at 14.00 from Wednesday April 25 1990. Monday to Thurs used in 1990/91, then daily at 13.45 in mid 1992
| Wednesday 14 October 1992 13.45
| [[A Country Practice]] 
|}

The Central pilot was slightly longer than the pilot on YTV and Border because slightly more advertising was permitted at the weekend than in weekday afternoons approaching children's television. In the event that Central had allocated too much time to the pilot, they would have screened a cartoon afterwards.

