| 11th to Complete 
| Completed 
| Completed 
|}
* Figures in '''bold''' indicate which region was furthest ahead of those still screening the programme at the very end of the year. 

1984
* No episodes screened anywhere on Good Friday 20 April. 

* Only STV had an episode on Tuesday 8 May 14.00. All 15.30 soaps removed from schedule (as day before, Bank Holiday)

* No episode on Wednesday 6 June (Derby Day)

1985
* The Budget on 19 March along with ITN News Special (VE Day) on 8 May and Derby Day 5 June meant no episodes were screened in any regions on these days in 1985.

* No episodes on Grampian on 8 and 9 August 1985.

* No episodes in any region on 23(only TVS 16.45), 24, 25, 26 and 27 December. 

1986
* During 1986, regions intending to screen episodes on 19 March (announcement of engagement of Sarah Ferguson and Prince Andrew) and 2 April (terrorist airline bomb) at 15.30 (15.25 TSW) had last minute changes to their schedule meaning that the episode intended for these dates were in fact screened on the next day (Thursday) instead. 

* No episodes in any region on Budget Day 18 March 1986.

* On Monday 21/04/86 a networked programme Happy Birthday Your Majesty meant that no regions screened any soaps at 15.30. Ulster were the only region to move their Sons and Daughters episode to 14.00 on that day. TVS and Channel were not affected as their episode was at 17.15, but their other 15.30 soap was affected. 

* Also no regions scheduled to screen an episode on Wednesday 23 July 1986 due to the Royal wedding of Sarah Ferguson and Prince Andrew.

* No epsodes in any region on 24 December 1986.

1988
* No episode on Border, Central, Channel, Granada, STV, TVS, TSW and YTV on Tuesday 15 March 1988 due to Budget.

* No episodes in any region on Easter Monday 4 April 1988. No episode on Border on 5 April.

* No episodes in any region on Derby Day 1 June 1988

* No episodes in any region on 26/27 December and no episodes on STV on 23 and 30 December 1988.

1989
* No episode on Border on 7 February due to The Young Doctors being moved out of it's Wednesday slot to allow Live Scottish football on 8 February.
* No episode on Grampian on 8 February due to live Scottish football.

1990 
No episodes on Granada on 11, 12, 25, 26 June and 10 and 11 December 1990. 

1993
* No episodes on Border on 24 and 30 August.

* No episode on Border on Wednesday 13 October due to Live Football. See Border above for other lost slots that year.

* All regions do not screen episodes at 15.30 on Derby Day which was usually the first Wednesday of June. All regions do not screen a 15.30/17.15 episode on the Tuesday where the Budget occurred, usually mid-March. Some Good Fridays episodes are screened, some network films are screened instead. No episodes are ever screened on 25, 26 December, 1 January in any region. Bank Holiday Mondays usually had no episodes screened in the 15.30/17.15/18.05 slots although on odd occasions episodes were screened. In some years Network programming filled the week between Christmas and New Year, on other years regions were free to play their own shows, most choosing Sons and Daughters or The Young Doctors, STV notably did not screen the show over the Xmas / New Year period.

