* Where the day is shown as '''Tue''' or '''Fri''' this signifies that this particular episode was the last of the week - meaning the longest gap between episodes.

* The longest amount of time that passed for an episode to be first shown and it's last showing was episode 971. It was first screened by Central on Friday 9 December 1988 at 15.30 and eventually aired on STV over six and a half years later on Thursday 27 July 1995 at 02.30.

==Remakes==
The series has inspired five [[remake]]s, going on fifth produced under license from the original producers and based, initially, on original story and character outlines. These are ''[[Verbotene Liebe]]'' (Germany, 1995- ); ''[[Skilda världar]]'' (Sweden, 1996-2002); ''[[Apagorevmeni agapi]]'' (Greece, 1998); ''[[Cuori Rubati]]'' (Italy, 2002-2003)  ''[[Zabranjena ljubav]]'' (Croatia, 2004- );

==DVD==

A DVD marking the 25th Anniversary of ''Sons and Daughters'' was released in October 2006.

Umbrella Entertainment have confirmed that they are in planning stage to release the complete series

Long standing cast member Tom Richards, who played David Palmer, released a DVD of interviews with fellow cast members in August 2007

